Purpose
This file stores and retrieves agent modules by typed agent name.

Linear intent
1. Define the hash-table key behavior for `Core_agent_name.t`.
2. Instantiate a hash-table module specialized to agent names.
3. Define the registry type as a table of packed agent modules.
4. Provide `create` so callers can choose an initial capacity.
5. Provide `register` so an agent module is inserted under its own typed id.
6. Provide `find` so the runtime engine can look up an agent by name.

